UserIdent is a user-recogniser using body-shape and voice.
It uses the kinect, OSCeleton and the Mistral-framework.

= Install =
 * Move userIdentHome to ~/.userIdent
 * Install Dependencies for OSCeleton, see https://github.com/avin2/SensorKinect
  * Install OpenNI
  * Install NITE
 * If not using Linux 32-Bit: 
  * replace the files in ~/.userIdent/bin with
    a new version of Mistral, see http://mistral.univ-avignon.fr/index_en.html
  * replace osceleton with a new version, see https://github.com/Sensebloom/OSCeleton

Now execute demo.sh or import into eclipse
